cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper proposes a framework for detecting action patterns and modeling sensory-motor relationships using a generative recurrent neural network. The paper focuses on two types of data, fruit fly behavior and online handwriting, which are both related to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a recurrent neural network suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The framework also has potential applications in robotics (cs.RO) for modeling and controlling behavior. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, and cs.RO.
